  "text": "LLVM Pass Manager Registration and Execution Chain\n\n## Overview\n\nThe LLVM optimization pass system uses two complementary mechanisms: the legacy pass manager (deprecated) and the new pass manager. Both are rooted in a centralized PassRegistry that tracks all available passes.\n\n## 1. PassManager Template System (New PM)\n\nThe core PassManager template is defined in `llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h` (lines 159-226). This is a template class parameterized by the IR unit it operates on (Module, Function, Loop, etc.). The PassManager template:\n- Stores a vector of passes (line 225) as `std::vector<std::unique_ptr<PassConceptT>> Passes`\n- Implements the `addPass()` method (lines 193-214) which stores passes using type erasure via PassModel\n- Contains a `run()` method that sequentially executes all contained passes\n- Two type aliases provided: `ModulePassManager` (line 238) and `FunctionPassManager` (line 247)\n\n## 2. PassRegistry System (Static Registration)\n\nThe PassRegistry is defined in `llvm/include/llvm/PassRegistry.h` and implemented in `llvm/lib/IR/PassRegistry.cpp`. This is a singleton that maintains two maps:\n- `PassInfoMap`: Maps pass type identifiers (&PassClass::ID) to PassInfo objects\n- `PassInfoStringMap`: Maps command-line argument strings to PassInfo objects\n\nThe `registerPass()` method (PassRegistry.cpp:48-62) inserts pass metadata and notifies registration listeners.\n\n## 3. Pass Registration Macros (Legacy PM)\n\nThe legacy pass registration mechanism uses macros defined in `llvm/include/llvm/PassSupport.h`:\n- `INITIALIZE_PASS` (lines 56-58): Expands to create registration code\n- `INITIALIZE_PASS_BEGIN/END` (lines 39-54): Creates a function that constructs PassInfo and calls `registry.registerPass()`\n- These macros generate static initialization functions that execute at program startup\n- `RegisterPass<T>` template (lines 89-98): Allows direct pass registration via global constructor\n\n## 4. PassInfo Metadata\n\nDefined in `llvm/include/llvm/PassInfo.h`, PassInfo stores:\n- Pass name (friendly display name)\n- Pass argument (command-line string like \"instcombine\")\n- Pass type ID (&ClassName::ID for RTTI)\n- Normal constructor function pointer\n- Analysis pass flag\n- CFG-only pass flag\n\n## 5. PassBuilder Pipeline Construction\n\nThe PassBuilder class in `llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h` is the primary interface for constructing optimization pipelines:\n\n### Key Methods:\n- `buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline()` (line 258-260): Entry point for O0/O1/O2/O3 pipelines\n- `buildModuleOptimizationPipeline()` (line 249-250): Constructs the core optimization pipeline (O2/O3)\n- `buildFunctionSimplificationPipeline()` (line 205-206): Constructs function-level optimizations\n- `buildModuleSimplificationPipeline()` (line 223-224): Module-level canonicalization passes\n\n## 6. O2/O3 Pipeline Execution Order\n\nThe O2/O3 optimization pipeline is constructed in `llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp` by the `buildModuleOptimizationPipeline()` function (starting at line 1478). The execution order includes:\n\n### Module-Level Passes (lines 1478-1660):\n1. `PartialInlinerPass()` - Partially inline large functions\n2. `EliminateAvailableExternallyPass()` - Remove available external functions\n3. `ReversePostOrderFunctionAttrsPass()` - Infer function attributes\n4. PGO instrumentation passes (if enabled)\n5. `RecomputeGlobalsAAPass()` - Recompute alias analysis\n\n### Function-Level Optimization Pipeline (lines 1660-1700):\nUsing FunctionPassManager that adds:\n1. `DropUnnecessaryAssumesPass()`\n2. `LoopVersioningLICMPass()` and `LICMPass()` (if enabled)\n3. `Float2IntPass()`\n4. `LowerConstantIntrinsicsPass()`\n5. `LowerMatrixIntrinsicsPass()` (if enabled)\n6. `ControlHeightReductionPass()` (O3 only)\n\n### Loop Optimization Pipeline (lines 1700-1750):\nUsing LoopPassManager:\n1. `LoopRotatePass()`\n2. `LoopDeletionPass()`\n3. `LoopInterchangePass()` (if enabled)\n4. Loop Fusion and Distribution passes\n\n### Vectorization and Backend Passes (lines 1750-1850):\n1. `addVectorPasses()` - Loop and SLP vectorization\n2. `LoopSinkPass()`\n3. `InstSimplifyPass()`\n4. `DivRemPairsPass()`\n5. `TailCallElimPass()`\n6. `SimplifyCFGPass()`\n\n### Final Global Optimizations (lines 1850-1900):\n1. `AllocTokenPass()`\n2. `HotColdSplittingPass()`\n3. `IROutlinerPass()`\n4. `GlobalDCEPass()`\n5. `ConstantMergePass()`\n6. `MergeFunctionsPass()` (if enabled)\n7. `CGProfilePass()`\n8. `RelLookupTableConverterPass()`\n9. `WholeProgramDevirtPass()` with devirtualization\n\n## 7. Static Pass Registry\n\nAll passes are catalogued in `llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def`, which defines:\n- MODULE_ANALYSIS: Module-level analysis passes\n- MODULE_PASS: Module-level transformation passes\n- CGSCC_ANALYSIS/CGSCC_PASS: Call graph SCC passes\n- FUNCTION_ANALYSIS/FUNCTION_PASS: Function-level passes\n- LOOP_ANALYSIS/LOOP_PASS: Loop-level passes\n\nThis file is included by PassBuilder to generate the pass registration and parsing infrastructure.\n\n## 8. Execution Flow\n\n1. **Initialization**: At startup, all passes call their INITIALIZE_PASS functions, registering themselves in PassRegistry\n2. **Pipeline Selection**: Frontend calls PassBuilder::buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline() with optimization level\n3. **Pipeline Construction**: PassBuilder methods construct nested PassManager objects, calling addPass() to add passes\n4. **Pipeline Execution**: ModulePassManager::run() is called with the module and AnalysisManager\n5. **Pass Execution**: Each pass is run sequentially via its operator()(Module&, ModuleAnalysisManager&)\n6. **Analysis Invalidation**: After each pass, the AnalysisManager invalidates analyses based on PreservedAnalyses\n\n## Key Integration Points\n\n- **PassManager Template** (`llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h`): Core template-based execution engine\n- **PassRegistry** (`llvm/include/llvm/PassRegistry.h/cpp`): Central pass metadata repository\n- **PassBuilder** (`llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h`): High-level pipeline construction API\n- **PassBuilderPipelines.cpp** (`llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp`): Implementation of optimization pipelines\n- **PassSupport.h** (`llvm/include/llvm/PassSupport.h`): Macros for pass registration\n- **PassRegistry.def** (`llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def`): Static declaration of all built-in passes"
